description:
The Snake Of Saigon!

The actual story of federal agent Clark Mason's single-handed battle against the most vicious spy ring in the far East... "The Snake of Saigon!"

Wanted: A Clue (Text Only Story)

The Secret of Comrade Petrov

Beneath the wet walls of Drukala prison, behind the Iron Curtain, a drama of life and death is played out and the stakes are the soul of a traitor and the fate of the country he betrayed!

Design for Death

Lisbon! International city of glamour, intrigue, and sudden death! Where a dress shop can become a battlefield and the latest fashion the last word in wholesale destruction!
name: The Snake Of Saigon!

description:
Roman Ratrace

On May 17, 1950, little did Clark Mason dream that in the mysterious ruins of Rome lurked the threat of deadly danger to his nation ....and his life!

Desert of Horror

Clark Mason fights his toughest battle for American freedom on the shores of Tripoli!

Counter-Spy! (Text Only Story)

The Bribe!

Here is a spy story told by an average American... Charles Johnson! Read what he did when a spy from behind the Iron Curtain tried to bribe him to betray America!

Sabotage!

Clark Mason found himself trapped in a net of foreign spies on the twelfth story of a New York skyscraper! Only a miracle saved him from death... what was that miracle?
name: Roman Ratrace

description:
The Silent Death!

Just as there are many ways a man can live... so there are infinite ways he can die! Especially on the battlefield where death strikes in a thousand forms! Sometimes with the Earth-shaking thunder of bombs! Sometimes in the sneakiest of silence! But I encountered in the Fall of 1951 an annihilation more swift than lightning, more quiet than the grave, yet more deadly than any weapon of destruction devised by man!

Shoeshine Spies (Text Only Story)

The Strange Enemy!

The Communist Army in Korea has used every trick in the book against the U.N. Forces... and a lot of tricks which haven't been written yet! One of their dirtiest tricks was the one they used in a battle North of Samdung!

The Human Target

War is tough, but it was tougher still for one G.I. who became... The Human Target

Captured!

There's one way to fight fire... with fire! But when it comes to double-crossers, a simple double-cross in return may not be enough! What you need is a triple-cross!
name: The Silent Death!

description:
The Secret Invasion

Last Spring, Uncle Sam had a close call! In fact the closest yet! While the red press was yelling peace, its cold-hearted agents were hacking out a horrible scheme in the frozen wastes of the North--how and why it never came off is the story of... The Secret Invasion!

Discs of Death

From the files of your F.B.I. comes this baffling case history that clearly illustrates how cunning and ruthless the trained operatives of our country's enemies can be! As you read this puzzling, action-packed tale, you'll realize why Jim Blaine, ace trouble-shooter of the F.B.I. remarked with grim humor, "this is one for the record!"

Treason on the High Seas (Text Only Story)

Date with Death

It wasn't that I was caught flat-footed or something! I knew what the setup was, but there was no going back! I had to go through with it... knowing that I was keeping a Date With Death!

The Secret of Hakim's Harem

"Cherchez la femme"... look for the woman... goes the old French saying! But in Turkey where women come in bunches... and so does murder... things get complicated! Especially when in Turkey' spy paradise... Istanbul! Too many important allied military men found their way to heaven... in a woman's arms!
name: The Secret Invasion

description:
The Red Terror!

The red terror was not only the scourge of our Korean armies! He was a mysterious killer whose cunning could be counted in the thousands of men he sent to their doom!

All Kinds Of Heroes (Text Only Story)

The Assassins

There is only one equivalent of a rattlesnake... a sniper! Both kill suddenly, without warning, and preferably when your back is turned! I should know... I turned my back once too often!

Surrender Leaflet

It was a bad day for the 203rd Artillery Battalion of the North Korean people's Army, but they were soon to find out that facing the Yank barrage was easier than facing their Chinese overlords...

The Phantom Reds!

The doggies in my outfit were tough, rugged soldiers! They slugged it out with the Reds on all kinds of battlefields! They knew they could hold their own against the enemy at the time... at least they felt that way until they came up against the Phantom Reds!
name: The Red Terror

description:
The Communist Zone

The Brandenburg Gate! It marked the demarcation point between the free peoples of West Berlin and the oppressed inhabitants of the Russian Zone! It was in the very shadows of this ominous structure that The Big Kidnap took place!

The Great Explosion!! (Text Only Story)

Contact In Ankara

The time... month of March... the place... somewhere in the Ural Mountains... the objective... Death for a secret agent of the Allied powers!

Dog Eat Dog!

The little, ordinary man you see above walking with his daughter and his dog, is Charles Smith, chemist! His name is a common one... he's just a nice, quiet, ordinary, rather timid American... yet he was a marked man... marked by the Communists!

5 Seconds To Disaster!

I've had many strange assignments with the Secret Service, but this was the first time my chief ordered me to play nursemaid to a bunch of merchant seamen from behind the Iron Curtain! The chief wanted to know what the seamen did in the port of New York during their 24-hour layover...
name: The Communist Zone
